comments.text:
"Are we truly tired of seeing dead Muslim children?"

If the answer is yes, we must realize that true change requires more than emotional responses or fleeting actions. Allah says in the Quran:
"Indeed, Allah will not change the condition of a people until they change what is within themselves" (Quran 13:11).

This means we must reflect on two things:

1. Our Individual Choices: Are we living according to the guidance of Allah, or are we prioritizing our desires and comforts over His commands? Real change begins when we align our lives with the principles of Islam, seeking Allah’s pleasure above all.


2. The System We Follow: True justice and peace cannot come from flawed, man-made laws. We must strive for the system that Allah has revealed—a system rooted in divine wisdom, justice, and mercy. Man-made systems will always fail because they are limited by human desires and biases.



If we want real change, we must actively work toward:

Living by Allah’s guidance in our personal lives.

Advocating for and implementing the systems Allah has revealed in our communities and beyond.


Posting on social media or expressing outrage is not enough. We need sincere action, collective effort, and a commitment to rejecting systems that contradict divine law. Change starts within, but it must grow to transform the structures around us. Only Allah’s system can bring the justice and peace we seek.
comments.author: @iGridCreativeWorks
